createConnection

public void createConnection(String[] parameters)
Creates a connection.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument the name for the connection,
parameters[2] argument is the is the RTSPServer port which handles the responses,
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
XTTProperties

startRTSPServer

public void startRTSPServer(String[] parameters)
starts the RTSPServer as an instance of RTSPServer.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument is the RTSPServer port,
parameters[2] argument is the RTSPServer timeout.
parameters[3] is the RTSPServer root directory,
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
RTSPServer, XTTProperties

stopRTSPServer

public void stopRTSPServer(String[] parameters)
stops all/one RTSPServers and all it's threads.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name, no additional parameters are requeired,
the optional parameters[1] argument is the RTSPServer port of the RTSPServer to stop, if omitted all running servers are stopped.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
RTSPServer.closeSocket(String), RTSPServer.closeSockets()

Parameters:

setServerReturnMessage

public void setServerReturnMessage(String[] parameters)
Overrides the normal RTSP Return Message with a custom code.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] is the Message after the response code including the whitespace between message and response code (for "RTSP/2.0 200 Ok" it would be " Ok").
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
